# Notebook version naming (scripts/ and output/ only)

This rule applies **only** to files created by the agent in **`scripts/`** and **`output/`**.

## Notebooks in scripts/

When creating a **new** Jupyter notebook in `scripts/`:
- Name it `vNNN_descriptive_name.ipynb`, with `NNN` a **three-digit** version number (e.g. `v000`, `v001`).
- The rest of the name can be descriptive. Each new notebook uses the next consecutive version number.

## Outputs in output/

When a notebook in `scripts/` writes files (plots, tables, summaries, FITS, ECSV, etc.) to `output/`:
- Those output files must start with the **same** `vNNN_` prefix as the notebook (e.g. notebook `v000_foo.ipynb` → outputs `v000_summary.md`, `v000_candidates.fits`).
- This makes it easy to see which outputs were produced by which notebook.

## This project

- Version numbering starts at **v000** for this project.
- The **next version to use** when creating a new notebook in `scripts/` is **v000**.
- After creating a notebook (e.g. `v000`), update this rule so the stated "next version" is **v001** (and so on).

## Scope

- Applies only to **new** notebooks created in `scripts/` and the **new** output files they write to `output/`.
- Does not apply to files in `src/`, `data/`, or elsewhere, or to existing files.
